\begin_layout Standard
This chapter presents an introduction to the general circulation of the
 atmosphere and Australia's regional teleconnections.
 Following this there is a literature review of the synoptic climatology
 of the Australian region.
 Included in the literature review are studies that examine variability
 through pressure and geopotential height fields, but also studies whose
 focus is on wind and/or solar variability.
 The covariability of wind and solar and how the covariability can be influenced
 by certain synoptic classifications is then explored.
\end_layout

