\begin_layout Standard
Of the publications that explore surface solar irradiance at the Earth surface,
 numerical models are widely used to describe the distribution of incoming
 and outgoing long- and short-wave components.
 It is noted by 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citet
key "Hatzianastassiou2005"

\end_inset

 that due to the sparsity of solar irradiance observations, extrapolation
 to larger/global scales is only possible with using model simulations.
 In Australia, 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citet
key "Liu2001"

\end_inset

 noted that of the some 16,000 weather stations across the continent only
 50 have any records of solar radiation, while nearly all stations have
 daily records of rainfall.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The components of the total solar radiation reaching the surface of the
 Earth that are of interest to solar power generation are the direct normal
 irradiance (DNI) (needed for concentrating solar power (CSP) and also utilised
 by Photo-Voltaic (PV) panels) and diffuse radiation (utilised by PV installatio
ns, but not CSP).
 A comprehensive investigation into the global surface radiation budget
 (using Downward Shortwave Radiation (DSR), the combination of direct and
 diffuse irradiance) was conducted by 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citet
key "Hatzianastassiou2005"

\end_inset

 using data from the International Satellite Cloud Climatology Project (ISCCP)
 (
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citealp
key "Schiffer1983"

\end_inset

).
 Modelling for the period 1984-2000, 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citet
key "Hatzianastassiou2005"

\end_inset

 found that DSR in the southern hemisphere (SH) tended to vary much more
 than the northern hemisphere (NH).
 The authors noted that this larger amplitude was primarily due to the earth-sun
 distance being a minimum in the SH summer and a maximum in the SH winter.
 However, the annual cycle is also modulated by subsidence regions and storm
 track positioning in the SH (
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citealp
key "Hatzianastassiou2005"

\end_inset

).
 
